d commands like MailFile with the left mouse button won't work.  The mode can be exited by placingthe cursor in the bottom window and clicking the left mouse button.     don*start*00586 00024 US Date: 3 Aug. 1981 2:20 pm PDT (Monday)From: Brotz.PASubject: Hermes and LeesburgIn-reply-to: Tanner's message of 3 Aug. 1981 12:07 pm PDT (Monday)To: Tannercc: LaurelSupportYou can send a message via Xerox Hermes by sending a Laurel message to<station code> @ XNET, where <station code> is the Hermes station code.  (Don'ttype the angle brackets.)There are many Altos in Leesburg, and they have their own message systemregistry, LB.  Check with your correspondents and determine whether you cansend your message directly to someone there.-- Doug*start*01890 00024 US Date: 23 June 1981 1:09 pm PDT (Tuesday)From: Schroeder.PASubject: Distribution lists: directory and request formTo: AllPA^.pa, AllES^.es, AllWBST^.wbstcc: Registrar.es, Registrar.pa, Registrar.wbstReply-To: SchroederThis message announces a hardcopy directory of public distribution lists from thees, pa, and wbst registries; and a Laurel form for requesting the creation of newdistribution lists.DIRECTORYThe file <Laurel>DLMap.press, stored on [Erie], [Iris], [Isis], [Ivy], [Oly],[Phylum], and [Rain], containes a printable listing of the publically availabledistribution lists in the es, pa, and wbst registries.  This press file hardcopys on~17 sides, and can be printed on your local press printer by chatting to thenearest file server (in the bottom window of Laurel 6) and using the "press"command.  You may find the listing a handy desk reference when trying todiscover which DL to send a message to.  It will also enable you to discover theexistence of DL you want to join.  A legend at the front of this directorydescribes how to read it and gives some advice on the use and maintenance ofDL's.  The listing will be updated ~ once a week, and is a snapshot of the DLstructures in the Grapevine data base.DL CREATION REQUEST FORMThe file <Laurel>DLRequest.form, stored  on the file servers mentioned above, isa form for requesting the creation of a new DL.  The form is specialized for eachregistry: "es" registry users should obtain it from [Isis], [Oly], or [Rain]; "pa"users from [Iris], [Ivy], or [Phylum]; "wbst" registry users from [Erie].  To usethis form, "Get" it into the bottom window of Laurel 6 and fill it in asinstructed.  Then "Deliver" it.  The form contains a description of the meaning ofthe vaious parameters associated with a DL.  Please use this form wheneverrequesting the creation of a new DL.*start*01912 00024 US Date: 14 July 1981 5:30 pm EDT (Tuesday)Sender: Axelrod.WBSTFrom: MCMail.WBSTSubject: Resumption of Monroe County Off-Net Mail Delivery ServiceTo: AllDLOS^.dlos, AllEOS^.eos, AllES^.ES, AllHENR^.henr, AllPA^.pa, AllWBST^.wbst, AllXRCC^.xrcccc: (Jim Ferro - CONC) MCMail, (Dave Lang - 102) MCMailReply-To: AxelrodThe Monroe County off-net mail delivery service, which had been inactive forsome time, has been resumed.  This service, provided by GSD Mail Services,allows a Grapevine message, appropriately addressed, to be delivered in hardcopyform to non-Grapevine addressees.  Similiar services exist in Palo Alto, ElSegundo, Pasadena and Dallas.Mail to off-net Monroe County locations should be addressed as 	(Name - location) MCMail.WBSTwhere "location" represents a valid Monroe county mail stop.  For example, tosend an off-net hardcopy to me in Building 128, address the message to	(Art Axelrod - 128) MCMail.WBST.In Laurel6, this format will print properly in either the "To:" field or the "cc:"field.  Any number of MCMail locations may be included in a single message.The information within the ( ) represents a "comment" field that will be printedout when a message is hardcopied from Laurel, while the MCMail.WBST is theGrapevine mailbox.Mail Services personnel wil read the MCMail.WBST mailbox, and transmithardopies, daily.Monroe County mail stops are usually buiding numbers.  These numbers havethe following significance:	001 - 029 = Xerox Square.  Ex: 007 is the 7th floor of Xerox Square	052 = Xerox Square Annex	CONC = Xerox Square Concourse	1xx, 2xx, 3xx = Buildings within the Webster Campus	8xx = Other Xerox sites in Monroe CountyFor details, see the Intelnet Telephone directory.The off-net services at other sites have proven quite successful.  Everyone isinvited to make full use of our service as well.   Art Axelrod*start*01377 00024 US Date: 17 July 1981 11:03 am EDT (Friday)Sender: Axelrod.WBSTFrom: MCMail.WBSTSubject: Off-Net Mail Services ListTo: AllDLOS^.dlos, AllEOS^.eos, AllES^.ES, AllHENR^.henr, AllPA^.pa, AllWBST^.wbst, AllXRCC^.xrcccc: (Jim Ferro - CONC) MCMail.WBST, (Dave Lang - 102) MCMail, (Joe Alhanati)ESMail.esReply-To: AxelrodThis is follow up to our recent announcement concerning the resumption off-netmail services in Monroe County.  Similiar services exist in El Segundo, Pasadenaand Dallas.  Contrary to our previous announcement, no such service currentlyexists in Palo Alto.Another correction:  Mail Services in Monroe County is administered by the RealEstate Division, rather than General Services Division, as stated.Grapevine users throughout the network are encouraged to use this servicefreely whenever appropriate.  For any questions concerning delivery at specificsites contact the individuals listed below.  -------------------			OFF-NET MAIL DELIVERY SERVICESSITE		MAILBOX		CONTACT	MAILBOX		INTELNETMonroe	MCMail.wbst	Art Axelrod	Axelrod.wbst		8*222-5811CountyEl Segundo	ESMail.es		Joe Alhanati	(Joe Alhanati)	8*823-7554							      ESMail.esXEOS		EOSMail.eos		Ron Gechman Gechman.eos	8*844-2016Dallas		DLOSMail.dlos	Bob Yost	Yost.dlos		8*723-6145Stored On: [erie]<NetSupport>Off-NetMail.list-------------------*start*01473 00024 US Date: 17 July 1981 9:44 am PDT (