 the Printer option in the hardcopy submenu (that's thePrinter, not the Form), must be set to the word Local.  When the Printer is Local,if the Form brackets are empty, then the HyType hardcopy form is used, if theForm brackets are non-empty, then the specified form is used.  This means justset the Printer to Local, and the rest is defaulted.HyType 11 refers to the RomanPS print wheel.  If you will be printing with adifferent type wheel, set Font: 9 ...  accordingly (with either HyType 10 forElite, HyType 12 for Pica.)To modify this form, use the rules given in the Laurel Manual, Appendix C.-- Doug*start*00267 00024 US Date: 20 July 1981 5:07 pm PDT (Monday)From: Barth.PASubject: Laurel featureTo: BrotzWhen one starts editing a message after running Cholla the Laurel delivercommand gets painted onto the screen, overwriting the Cholla deliver command.*start*00682 00024 US Date: 5 Aug. 1981 11:20 am PDT (Wednesday)From: Gifford.PASubject: Mode in Modeless LaurelTo: BrotzDoug,I was suprised to find that there was a mode in Laurel that confused me.  Iclicked "Hardcopy", and then changed the printer I wanted to print on.  Then Idecided not to hardcopy after all.  None of the other buttons on the screen wouldrespond until I aborted the Hardcopy.  Why can't "Cancel" be eliminiated?On another topic, my little finger sometimes hits the button to the right of "BS". I almost passed out the first time I saw my 2000 character messsage disappearwhen I only wanted to delete a single character.A faithful fan,Dave*start*01481 00024 US Date: 6 Aug. 1981 7:22 am PDT (Thursday)From: RONFREEMAN.ESSubject: Error Report(Last sentence corrected)To: LaurelSupport.PAI wanted to save part of a news item I had received over the net into a file Ihave on taxes.  I "Moved" the entire message to a file I named junk.mail.  I then did a "Get" to put it into my lower window so I could delete all the extraneousjunk.  Then I did a "Put" and overwr