asinter, LaurelImp^I have read your memo on file access, and in general agreethat the proposed measures are important for shoring upsome of the more gaping holes in the Internet security.The only problem and reduction in functionality is yourproposal for disallowing "function" login names such asSDSupport. I agree that for access control that these pseudo-names should not have any access authorization.One simple solution would be for laurel to allow (and make it easy)for person A to send out mail that says "From: B" AND WHICHDOES NOT HAVE "Sender: A" appended in the case where B'smail is forwarded to A.I don't think this introduces any particular security holes,and it also provides a way to achieve something which wouldotherwise require giving out one's password: "Please answermy mail for me (as me) when I am out of town."Larry*start*02820 00024 US Date: 11 Feb. 1982 5:05 pm PST (Thursday)From: Brotz.PATo: CrowtherSubject: Laurel module breakdowncc: BrotzModule name			Size			Category				S: < 10K bytes,	(OK, Minimal Rewrite,				M: < 30K bytes,	Major Rewrite, Cedar provides,				L: >= 30K bytes	Goes away)AccessOp				S			Minimal RewriteAnswerImpl				M			OKAppendOp				S			Minimal RewriteBackStop				M			Cedar providesChollaBBoard			M			Minimal RewriteChollaCmd				M			Minimal RewriteChollaMail				M			Minimal RewriteChollaMailUtils			M			Minimal RewriteChollaMDControl			S			OKChollaSpecs				S			Minimal RewriteChollaStep				L			Minimal RewriteChollaStepList			M			Minimal RewriteChollaStepListParse			S			OKCopyOp				S			OK, Cedar providesCoreImpl				M			OKCoreStreams				M			OKDisplay				M		Major Rewrite, Cedar providesDMSTime				S			Minimal RewriteEditorDisplay			L			Cedar providesEditorFiles				M			Cedar providesEditorFind				M			Cedar providesEditorMain				M			Cedar providesEditorMisc				S			Cedar providesEditorTypein			S			Cedar providesEditorUndo				S			Cedar providesExecIO				S			Cedar providesExecKeyboard			S