l runnable program Print.laurel has beenresuscitated.This message describes only changes since the previous alpha test release.If no serious problems are discovered, the formal release of Laurel 6.1 will takeplace on Monday, June 6, after which we hope never to change Laurel again.Installing LaurelThis alpha test version of Laurel is called Laurel 6.1T38.  It has been stored indirectory <Laurel>6.1T38> on the following file servers:	Cactus, Erie, Ivy, Oly, Rain, RoseBowlTo install the new Laurel, use FTP to retrieve the file <Laurel>6.1T38>Laurel.cmfrom one of the above servers.  Then Quit to the Executive and issue thecommand:	> @Laurel.cmThis will obtain the new version of Laurel itself, as well as updated versions ofany Laurel-runnable programs already present on your disk.  When it isfinished, it will start Laurel.Changes to Laurel runnable programs-- Print.laurel generates hardcopy of files on your local disk or on a file server;the file may be an existing Press file, plain-text file, or Bravo file. Documentation may be found in file <Laurel>6.1T38>Print.doc.  (This programwas contributed by Ken <Pier.pa>.)Disposition of bugs reported prior to Laurel 6.1T38  1. REJECTED.  Display never appears; 3K RAM, 256K memory (Pellar.es). Unreproducible, probably hardware problem.  2. FIXED.  Kal doesn't work on non-XMesa Altos.  Added test at startup.  3. FIXED.  Basic requires latest microcode (floating point).  Added test atstartup.  4. FIXED.  Changing mail file name from RemoteTTY doesn't refresh Mail filebrackets.  5. FIXED.  Insert leaves hourglass in cursor (Replace also).  6. FIXED.  ForwardSpaceWord past end of composed message crashes Laurel;end test incorrect.  7. FIXED.  E ESC to LocalTTY editor crashes it.  8. FIXED.  Disk full and disk error crash Laurel in some situations (e.g., "Moveto"), whereas they were caught and handled gracefully in Laurel 6.  9. FIXED.  Hardcopy sometimes hangs on 64K Alto -- needs another VMbuffer.  Added code to release VM buffers for message objects when any menucommand is issued.  10. FIXED.  Explicit remote Run doesn't always default extension to .laurel.  11. FIXED.  Bogus date in SortMail crashes it.  12. FIXED.  Free disk page count updated too often -- really slows thingsdown.  13. FIXED.  ArpaGateway registry should be treated the same as ARPA.  14. REJECTED.  LocalTTY discards typescript at Quit time.  This is a feature:it's preserving the composed message left behind by the TTY editor.  15. FIXED.  Editing is too slow on 64K Altos.  Improved somewhat by shrinkingVM buffer pool.  Added DisplayLines profile option for shrinking bit map.  16. FIXED. Thumbing TOC of empty mail file hangs Laurel.  17. FIXED. Grapevine operations slow (esp. Maintain).  Enlarged routing cache.  18. FIXED.  Laurel occasionally trashes mail files on Dolphins.  ChangedLaurelByteBlt not to use BITBLT on Dolphin because this use of it apparentlydoes not work.  19. OPEN.  Scrolling composition window while runnable program is puttingtext into it occasionally breaks Laurel.  Suspect inadequate synchronization;probably too hard to fix.  20. FIXED.  Running Laurel immediately after quitting from Smalltalk-80 onDolphins doesn't work.  21. FIXED.  Hitting end-of-file while parsing mail stamp results in uncaughtcsD.EndOfStream.  22. FIXED.  Blue button New mail doesn't index the messages if disk space isexhausted during retrieval.  23. FIXED.  Hardcopy and Forward operate on all selected messages even ifthey are deleted.  This is a change from Laurel 6.  Nobody knows why thechange was made.  Changed it back.  24. FIXED.  Laurel still garbles mail files on Dolphins (16-word blocks at16-word boundaries).  Long-standing Alto/Mesa microcode bug -- programmedaround it.  25. REJECTED.  NetPrint.laurel (not maintained by LaurelSupport) no longerruns because Laurel's GFT has insufficient extra entries.  Enlarging it at allwould cost another page of resident storage, which is bad for 64K machines.  26. FIXED.  Attempting to move deleted message to nonexistent mail file causesLaurel to crash.  27. OPEN.  RemoteTTY and LocalTTY do not keep the display consistent withthe state of the mail file.  This is hard to fix.  28. FIXED.  Replace, unlike Insert, leaves the composed message marked ashaving been edited since last saved.Reporting problemsIf you encounter any problems with Laurel 6.1 or with the Laurel runnableprograms that are supported, please notify LaurelSupport.PA as usual.  Youshould mention that you are running Laurel 6.1T38 (bug reports generatedautomatically by Laurel contain this information already).	The Laurel Implementors*start*00951 00024 US Date: Sat, 28 May 83 16:15 PDTFrom: Stiles.esSubject: Re: Third Laurel 6.1 alpha test releaseIn-reply-to: "Taft.PA's message of Sat, 28 May 83 14:38 PDT"To: LaurelSupport.PAcc: StilesI have encountered a couple more full disk type problems, still present in 6.1T38:1.	With ~12 free disk pages left I went to maintain.laurel and did a TypeDetails on LaurelAlphaTest^.pa; this was large enough to go to zero pages andcause an uncaught signal 33201B with arg. 177777B.  I think when I clicked Red+ Blue per the instructions I went back to Alto Executive.2.	With 0 pages calling Laurel/c with mail pending get message:  Systemerror encountered.  Laurel cannot proceed. Click Yellow for automatic errorreporting.  However, when yellow is clicked I hear disk movement one time,then apparent death occurs:  Time report doesn't increment; possibly the cursorstill tracks the mouse.  Had to reboot.Bill <Stiles.es>*start*00946 00024 US Date: Sun, 5 Jun 83 15:22 PDTFrom: Taft.PASubject: End of Laurel 6.1 alpha testTo: LaurelAlphaTest^.paReply-to: LaurelSupport.paThe alpha test of Laurel 6.1 has ended.  Laurel 6.1 is now in the process of beinginstalled on file servers, and a general announcement will be made when this iscompleted (we hope within