e.  The indexingsucceeds only if the table of contents will fit in the disk space made available bydeleting the message that was being retrieved when the disk overflowed.It's not possible to predict when disk space will be exhausted, since the pagecount in the disk descriptor is only a hint.  The algorithm outlined above is theonly one I can think of that would work.  I probably would have changed thecode to use that algorithm if I had seen how it's currently being done.  But it'stoo late now.....	Ed Taft*start*00853 00024 US Date: Fri, 10 Jun 83 10:51 PDTFrom: Rumph.eosSubject: Error ReportTo: LaurelSupport.PAI was using the LocalTTY editor.  I typed "h<ESC>", and laurel bombedimmediately.  (I expect that the editor's command parser fell off the endexpecting something after the "h".  I had just deleted the previous editing withthe command "0jhkht<ESC>".Laurel 6.1  Dolphin (012#340#) with XMcode using XM MDS: 00 Banks: 177777Signal 056401 in IntExceptionsmsg 000001, msg^                            BackStop, 003405Signaller, 000521IntExceptions, 000223VirtCM, 000205VirtCom, 000207LaurelTTYEditor, 015053LaurelTTYEditor, 001257LaurelTTYEditor, 000614LaurelTTYInterface, 002024LocalTTYDriver, 000267LocalTTYDriver, 000115Modules, 000277Modules, 000157ExecSS, 000753ExecSS, 000436ExecSS, 000301Stack end OurProcess*start*00579 00024 US Date: Mon, 13 Jun 83 14:47 EDTFrom: SHEN.WBSTSubject: Error ReportTo: LaurelSupport.PAI was using NetPrint to print a Bravo file. Everything seemed to be workingbefore laurel quit.Laurel 6.1  Alto II XM (124#066#) with 3K Ram XMcode using XM MDS: 00Banks: 170000 code: 000051Signal 004605 in Modulesmsg 000001, msg^                            BackStop, 003405Signaller, 000521Modules, 000635Modules, 001261PupSockets, 000143PupPktCool, 003544PupPktCool, 000460PupByteStreams, 000314PupListeners[375B], 000702Stack end OurProcess*start*00812 00024 US Date: Wed, 15 Jun 83 09:42 PDTFr