 don'tbelieve it extends over more than 3 or 4 pages at a time.I believe this explains the difference in performance when deleting a messagefrom the middle of a big mail file.  I don't know why the change was made; butit's too late to do anything about it now.	Ed*start*00636 00024 US Date: Thu, 7 Jul 83 14:10 EDTFrom: Dusel.WBSTSubject: Error ReportTo: LaurelSupport.PAI clicked new mail blue after my disk overflowed with a normal mail retrieval. Laurel died during the "one at a time" retrieval.Laurel 6.1  Alto II XM (065#100#) with 3K Ram XMcode using XM MDS: 00Banks: 140000 code: 000051Signal 056401 in IntExceptionsmsg 000001, msg^                            BackStop, 003405Signaller, 000521IntExceptions, 000223AccessOp, 002061IntMailCom, 001120IntTrackMain, 001725IntTrackMain, 001252IntTrackMain, 001112IntTrackMain, 000704LaurelNub, 000126DebugNub, 000334*start*00576 00024 US Date: Fri, 8 Jul 83 09:10 PDTFrom: GMEREDITH.ESSubject: Error ReportTo: LaurelSupport.PAHad invoked 'New Mail' command.  Just starting out for the morning.Laurel 6.1  Alto II XM (056#166#) with 3K Ram XMcode using XM MDS: 00Banks: 140000 code: 000051Signal 056401 in IntExceptionsmsg 000001, msg^                            BackStop, 003405Signaller, 000521IntExceptions, 000223AccessOp, 002061IntMailCom, 001120IntTrackMain, 001725IntTrackMain, 001252IntTrackMain, 001112IntTrackMain, 000704LaurelNub, 000126DebugNub, 000334*start*00708 00024 US Date: Fri, 8 Jul 83 14:58 PDTFrom: JWeaver.PASubject: Error ReportTo: LaurelSupport.PASelected approximately four messages and bugged hardcopy so that messageswould be printed in Archive format.Laurel 6.1  Alto II XM (060#344#) with 2K Rom XMcode using XM MDS: 00Banks: 160000 code: 000051Signal 000201 in Residentmsg 106202, msg^ 045152 046541 062145 071054BackStop, 003405Signaller, 000521Resident, 001407IntHardcopyCom, 003745IntHardcopyCom, 003454IntHardcopyCom, 003132IntHa